More evidence of possible improper conduct against former Transnet CEO Brian Molefe was presented at the Inquiry into State Capture today. Former Transnet employee, Gerhard van der Westhuizen said Molefe circumvented Procurement processes when he awarded Transnet’s master service contract to a company linked to Gupta-family associate, Salim Issa. He says Molefe overturned a decision taken by Transnet’s recommending officers to award the contract to Neotel.  Molefe was Group CEO at Transnet before he became Group CEO at Eskom. More on this story at: 